                <head>No. 472.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RB1" type="from"
                            >Beardsley</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="to"
                            >Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Agency and Consulate-General of the United States
                                of America at Alexandria, Egypt</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 25, 1873</date>. (Received March
                        25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 68.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report at this late day that
                    the United States sloop of war Hartford arrived at Port Saïd on the 8th ultimo,
                    and sailed from Suez for China on the 18th ultimo. I presume Mr.
                        <persName>Page</persName> has already reported the arrival and departure of
                    the Hartford, as well as the particulars of her passage through the canal. As
                    Mr. <persName>Page</persName> does not-send his dispatches through this office,
                    I deem it prudent, even at this date, to report the Hartford’s movements, that
                    there may be no doubt of the information having been communicated to the
                    Department.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RB1">R. BEARDSLEY</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
